What other grown men
would be so consumed by their own vanity?

12:12.858 --> 12:15.319
Close the door! They can smell the decay!

12:15.319 --> 12:17.446
It's just Mitch and Cam.

12:17.446 --> 12:19.448
We were afraid you were
one of the beautiful boys.

12:19.448 --> 12:21.074
Please, I've never felt so hairy.

12:21.158 --> 12:24.119
Get in line,
this queen only has one trimmer.

12:24.203 --> 12:26.496
Okay, how horrible is this party?

12:26.580 --> 12:30.250
I'm a skinny little girl with twig arms.
It's all anyone's talking about.

12:30.334 --> 12:31.835
I told some twink by the crudite

12:31.919 --> 12:33.754
that I was swollen
from a kidney transplant.

12:33.754 --> 12:34.963
Well, then you have an excuse.

12:35.047 --> 12:36.173
Let me on that elliptical!

12:36.173 --> 12:38.800
I haven't felt this white
since I loved the movie <i>Green Book...</i>

12:38.884 --> 12:40.010
All right, bronzer me!

12:40.010 --> 12:42.304
And I don't want you to be stingy.
I want it everywhere.

12:42.304 --> 12:43.639
Everywhere!

12:45.891 --> 12:50.354
<i>I replaced the sign and attached
Stella's GPS tracker to the back.</i>

12:50.354 --> 12:52.773
<i>And then I headed home to Jay.</i>

12:54.441 --> 12:56.693
<i>- Hello!</i>
- Hey, honey. You get my text?

12:56.902 --> 13:00.531
I did. An eggplant and a peach emoji.

13:00.531 --> 13:02.533
Does that mean what I think it means?

13:02.533 --> 13:06.078
You bet. I ordered eggplant
parmesan and peach cobbler.

13:06.078 --> 13:08.372
Yum! I'll be home in a few minutes.

13:08.372 --> 13:10.249
<i>- Ay!</i>

13:10.415 --> 13:13.961
<i>- What?</i>
- Uh, nothing. I have a flat tire.

13:13.961 --> 13:16.046
I'm gonna call AA to get it fixed.

13:16.046 --> 13:17.840
No, AAA fixes tires.

13:17.840 --> 13:21.552
AA is that alcoholic cult
that makes your friends no fun anymore.

13:21.552 --> 13:22.886
I'll come fix the tire.

13:22.970 --> 13:24.263
No, no, no. I'll do it.

13:24.263 --> 13:26.139
This is another work thing, isn't it?

13:26.223 --> 13:29.184
I am losing you. I am in a tunnel.

13:29.268 --> 13:30.727
There's no tunnels!

13:32.271 --> 13:35.315
I can't believe I even
considered that for you!

13:35.399 --> 13:39.069
Alls I'm saying is,
the other families had alibis,

13:39.069 --> 13:42.656
and you wouldn't be
the first mother-son crime duo in history.

13:42.656 --> 13:45.784
I told you, Phil,
we didn't steal your sign.

13:45.868 --> 13:47.411
We slept in this morning.

13:47.411 --> 13:49.830
Mother and I went clubbing last night.

13:49.997 --> 13:52.749
We went looking for a husband,
but lost ourselves on the dance floor.

13:52.833 --> 13:55.252
Nice try, but I'm not buying
what you're selling.

13:55.460 --> 13:56.461
Confess!

13:56.545 --> 13:58.088
I can do this all day or...

14:00.007 --> 14:01.675
Six more times!

14:01.675 --> 14:04.761
Phil! I'm tracking the thief
that stole our sign!

14:04.845 --> 14:06.305
Hurry! He's getting away!

14:08.724 --> 14:12.019
I guess this new information
bursts my balloon.

14:12.019 --> 14:13.187
I bid you good day.

14:14.646 --> 14:16.440
Well, somebody should enjoy this.

14:16.440 --> 14:18.192
- I'm hungry.
- Stella!

14:20.319 --> 14:23.363
She's probably down the street,
playing with that greasy Chihuahua.

14:23.447 --> 14:24.448
Where did I go wrong?

14:24.448 --> 14:26.408
Why doesn't she know she deserves better?

14:26.408 --> 14:27.910
I think I have some
old cheese puffs in my room.

14:28.994 --> 14:31.413
Damn it, how'd you get
all the way across town?

14:31.413 --> 14:32.789
I'm coming, baby!

14:33.123 --> 14:34.124
I'm coming!

14:40.255 --> 14:42.090
Hey, Jay... Eh.

14:46.011 --> 14:47.179
Alex, what are you doing?

14:47.179 --> 14:50.474
Turning down this job
before corporate evil corrodes my insides.

14:50.474 --> 14:54.061
And I am not leaving my babies so that
I can be this stressed and miserable.

14:54.061 --> 14:55.145
I'm going to jail!

14:55.229 --> 14:57.397
I signed things without reading them!
What if I helped the pervs?

14:57.481 --> 14:58.941
What if I put the gun in their hand?

14:58.941 --> 15:00.400
Doesn't sound like
it was a gun in their hand.

15:00.484 --> 15:01.902
Solid.

15:01.902 --> 15:05.155
Well, it's been a great 40 years.

15:05.239 --> 15:08.575
In the words of my tattoo, "Peace out."

15:09.701 --> 15:10.702
Well...

15:10.911 --> 15:11.912
Margaret!

15:12.246 --> 15:14.873
Oh, it's okay.
I don't work here anymore.

15:14.957 --> 15:16.750
- Yeah, I'm out too.
- Yeah, I'm not going down with this ship.

15:16.834 --> 15:18.001
No, no, no. Stop. No one's leaving.

15:18.085 --> 15:19.920
We're not going to let one little misstep

15:19.920 --> 15:23.090
make us forget everything
this company has given us!

15:23.090 --> 15:25.801
I loved being a stay-at-home mom. I did.

15:25.801 --> 15:29.429
But working here has given me
a whole new sense of self.

15:29.847 --> 15:32.933
And, come on,
one mistake doesn't make us evil.

15:32.933 --> 15:34.309
We will come clean.

15:34.393 --> 15:37.187
We'll recall the product.
We'll do whatever we have to do.

15:37.271 --> 15:41.859
Because under this tech BS,
there is a company we love.

15:42.401 --> 15:44.945
Look, we may no longer make smart closets,

15:44.945 --> 15:48.073
but we're sure as hell
going to make smart closets.

15:48.240 --> 15:49.241
Mmm-hmm. Yeah.

15:49.241 --> 15:51.285
<i>Looking for a smart outfit?</i>

15:51.285 --> 15:55.038
<i>Maintain eye contact
with the mirror</i><i>and begin stripping down.</i>

15:55.539 --> 15:56.999
I deeply regret that.

16:01.128 --> 16:02.296
<i>Approaching Stella.</i>

16:02.296 --> 16:04.006
Look! That's him! On the bike!

16:04.006 --> 16:05.090
He's going off-road!

16:05.174 --> 16:08.010
Don't worry.
I'm gonna catch this guy or die trying!

16:08.010 --> 16:09.303
I love your enthusiasm.

16:09.303 --> 16:11.597
One note, and this might be
a second language thing,

16:11.597 --> 16:12.848
but when you say "die"...

16:12.848 --> 16:15.350
No, no, no! He's getting away!

16:18.103 --> 16:19.271
Freeze!

16:19.897 --> 16:20.898
Jay?

16:21.732 --> 16:23.984
What a ray of light in a dark time.

16:23.984 --> 16:26.028
Shut up, Phil. Where's my dog?

16:26.028 --> 16:28.363
And what are you doing here?
I thought you had a flat tire.

16:28.447 --> 16:32.117
I had to catch the thief
that was stealing Phil's signs,

16:32.201 --> 16:34.912
so I put Stella's tracking thing on it.

16:34.912 --> 16:38.332
What? What if she's down the street
with that over-sexed Chihuahua?

16:38.332 --> 16:41.502
Jay, she needs it,
and you can't be her everything!

16:41.502 --> 16:44.296
Turn around, punk!
I want to see your face!

16:46.048 --> 16:47.049
Sam?

16:47.049 --> 16:49.760
Why are you stealing signs
from your own house?

16:50.093 --> 16:51.094
Oh.

16:51.553 --> 16:53.138
You don't want to move.

16:53.222 --> 16:54.765
I don't want to leave my friends.

16:55.057 --> 16:58.435
I get it. Change is hard.

16:58.602 --> 17:01.063
When I moved to this country,
it was change.

17:01.063 --> 17:04.608
When I got married and moved
to a mainly white neighborhood

17:04.608 --> 17:08.987
with kind of racist lawn statues,
that was change.

17:09.071 --> 17:13.575
But we get to meet new people,
and we get to do new things that we love.

17:13.659 --> 17:15.911
Twelve years ago,
I didn't know these people,

17:15.911 --> 17:18.455
and now, I would kill for them.

17:18.622 --> 17:20.415
You will find people like that, too.

17:20.499 --> 17:22.251
- I hope you're right.
- I am.

17:22.251 --> 17:23.335
So, now, let's go.

17:23.335 --> 17:25.337
Put that bike in my car,
and I'll drive you home.

17:28.131 --> 17:30.717
Gloria, that was so terrific.

17:30.801 --> 17:35.430
I know! I am wonderful!
Why don't you want to hire me?

17:35.514 --> 17:38.016
Because I was worried that
it was a hobby to you,

17:38.100 --> 17:41.812
something to do till you got bored, but,
today, you really showed me something.

17:42.145 --> 17:43.480
- You're giving me the job?
- Yeah.

17:44.690 --> 17:46.900
This means that I'm gonna
have to work more...

17:46.984 --> 17:49.987
It's fine. If Sam can handle change,
so can I.

17:49.987 --> 17:53.115
Welcome to Dunphy Realty, Ms. Delgado.

17:53.115 --> 17:56.994
Delgado? That's your working name?
Man, the hits just keep coming.

17:57.995 --> 18:00.664
Okay. Before I do more,
does this look natural?

18:00.664 --> 18:04.126
That's a tricky word because the color
orange does appear in nature.

18:04.668 --> 18:06.128
Well, there you all are!

18:06.128 --> 18:09.173
Look, I love you, but you are literally
the only six people here

18:09.173 --> 18:10.674
I don't want in my bedroom.

18:10.674 --> 18:13.302
Thanks. We weren't feeling
insecure enough already.

18:13.302 --> 18:14.636
You know what I think?

18:14.720 --> 18:19.600
You only invited us because we make you
look like the hot old guy.

18:19.600 --> 18:20.684
Old guy? I'm not old!

18:20.684 --> 18:22.686
Oh, please,
hide that hairline all you want,

18:22.686 --> 18:25.898
we know what year you danced
on that Paula Abdul tour,

18:25.898 --> 18:27.024
and so do they.

18:27.024 --> 18:28.483
Oh, my God.

18:28.567 --> 18:31.653
I'm making a fool out of myself, aren't I?
Straight up, now tell me...

18:31.737 --> 18:33.655
Hi, honey.
Lily?

18:33.739 --> 18:35.199
- Hey, girl, hey.
- I knew it.

18:35.199 --> 18:36.283
You're hiding.

18:36.283 --> 18:38.493
- No. They are.
- No. No. They are, but we're not. No.

18:38.577 --> 18:40.913
So I'm supposed to love who I am,
but you guys don't?

18:40.913 --> 18:42.039
Hypocrites.

18:44.124 --> 18:45.250
Tough love time?

18:45.334 --> 18:47.544
We dig her. It comes off a little mean.

18:47.628 --> 18:49.379
She's not mean. She's right!

18:49.463 --> 18:52.007
I mean, why are we so obsessed
with how we look?

18:52.007 --> 18:53.800
So people will have sex with us?

18:53.884 --> 18:56.512
But confidence is the sexiest thing.

18:56.512 --> 18:58.180
That sounds stupid, doesn't it?

18:58.180 --> 19:00.516
I'm sorry. Look at someone else!

19:00.516 --> 19:03.685
Okay, but you know what?
Confidence is the most important thing,

19:03.769 --> 19:05.812
and, look, maybe we've lost
a little of our beauty,

19:05.896 --> 19:07.397
but we have a lot to be proud of.

19:07.481 --> 19:09.399
I'm a vice-principal. I'm a dad.

19:09.483 --> 19:11.818
I'm the city's first
openly-gay football coach.

19:11.902 --> 19:13.612
And... And I'm a state prosecutor.

19:13.612 --> 19:16.448
Ronaldo has a business and a family.

19:16.532 --> 19:17.824
And Bobby...

19:17.908 --> 19:22.037
I mean, sure, his career is not on fire,
but he looks great, and he's 50.

19:22.037 --> 19:24.873
I'm 37, you wicked old witch!

19:25.123 --> 19:26.959
I hear what you're saying,
but the point...

19:26.959 --> 19:30.546
Hey! The point is, at our age,

19:30.546 --> 19:34.466
we have earned the right to be
comfortable with who we are.

19:34.716 --> 19:36.260
Now, let's get out there,

19:36.260 --> 19:40.180
set good examples for our children
and our overly pampered pets!

19:41.306 --> 19:42.891
You with me?

20:14.590 --> 20:16.091
Whoo-hoo!

20:18.260 --> 20:19.511
<i>The older we get,</i>

20:19.595 --> 20:21.930
<i>the harder it is to keep up
with life's changes.</i>

20:22.890 --> 20:27.436
<i>We hold on to who we once were,
like it's the only way</i><i>we can be happy.</i>

20:30.814 --> 20:32.858
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

20:32.858 --> 20:35.819
<i>But there are huge
rewards when we take risks,</i>

20:35.903 --> 20:37.487
<i>embrace new experiences...</i>

20:38.155 --> 20:39.907
I am a proud middle-aged man.

20:39.907 --> 20:41.241
This is what I look like,

20:41.325 --> 20:42.743
and I think I look sexy...

20:45.871 --> 20:48.123
Am I literally invisible to you people?

20:50.792 --> 20:52.961
You know, I'm so proud of us.

20:53.045 --> 20:54.338
We overcame a lot today.

20:54.338 --> 20:56.673
Yeah, you know, I feel so much
lighter without all that shame.

20:56.757 --> 20:58.133
Although I guess it wouldn't hurt us

20:58.217 --> 20:59.801
if we were actually lighter.

20:59.885 --> 21:03.222
Yeah, I mean, we could exercise
more and both eat better.

21:03.222 --> 21:05.849
It would help if we got rid of
some of these temptations, you know?

21:05.933 --> 21:08.185
We don't need three
different kinds of pasta.

21:08.185 --> 21:11.772
Right. And parmesan cheese,
heavy cream...

21:11.772 --> 21:13.857
It's just empty calories and fat.

21:16.693 --> 21:18.570
We're totally making fettuccini alfredo,
aren't we?

21:18.654 --> 21:20.280
Damn straight. We don't have
another pool party for months.

21:20.364 --> 21:21.865
- I'll salt the water.
- I'm gonna get wine.
